  <discussion>Variety compacta has leaf hairs sufficiently dense to give the plants a gray-green to even whitish appearance; the plants are therefore similar to individuals of Heterotheca echioides, which is radiate. It occurs scattered in the Klamath, Cascade, and Coastal Range mountains of northern California.</discussion>
